  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Contribute to strenghten capacity of local health staff in KAYANZA to efficiently prevent community</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will target the province of Kayanza. It is the most population density in densely populated area and a business hub in the country. People from this province are famously known from their migration the most both in other provinces and even neighbouring countries.    This movement in the area makes the province hotspot  area and at risk of COVID-19, especially that one of the seven with detected provinces with detected case of COVID-19, that is Bukinanyana-Mabay- shares border with it as per June 20 MoH situation report. With its border with Rwanda. .</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Health service providers are the most at risk and  affected by the pandemic and need to be supported on some individual protection kits. For instance, out of the confirmed cases, 16.7% are health service providers as per the MoH situation reprot of June 20, 2020. Thus , health providers from 3 hospitals and 44 health centers will be trained on IPC-Infection Prevention Control in addition to 455 Community Health Workers-CHW, who in turn will reach 4,550 people. Burundian people live day by day and could have faced to the issue of accessing to Health services in covid-19 synthoms as soon as possible.</narrative>
  </description>
